<subSubSection id="644534326619FE86DE57AE67AFF69073" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B567870B6A2A3AFF315406CCC3863B6D" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8501F7D11B06B1206B58F92209CD20E" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation id="E5C5D3B50CB53DF2403FC1DDCA37C45B" author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Thessaloniki" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Συστηματική και βιονομική μελέτη των μακροβενθικών πολυxαίτων (AnnelidaPolychaeta) του Βορείου Αιγαίου" year="1994">Arvanitidis (1994)</bibRefCitation>
based on a single specimen. Type locality: Mediterranean (Banyuls-sur-Mer, France). 
<bibRefCitation id="94CFEC98917750BF6FC65868E5093C06" author="Pleijel, Fredrik" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="89 - 163" title="Phylogeny and classification of Hesionidae (Polychaeta)" volume="27" year="1998">Pleijel (1998)</bibRefCitation>
considers the species a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="66A5A063CC0A73AD895F62802802E586" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Podarkeopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Podarkeopsis arenicolus" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="arenicolus">Podarkeopsis arenicolus</taxonomicName>
(La Greca, 1946) but does not provide details and does not formalise the synonymy. As 
<bibRefCitation id="1F0691427DDA62D1E49B969DE129D260" author="Rizzo, Alexandra Elaine" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="267 - 291" title="Hesionidae Grube, 1850 (Annelida: Polychaeta) from South-Southeastern Brazil, with descriptions of four new species" volume="3856" year="2014">Rizzo and Salazar-Vallejo (2014)</bibRefCitation>
list both species in their key and recognise difference in the size of the eyes, length of the median antenna and chaetal details, the species is therefore treated as valid here, pending further information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
